{"type":"message","id":"1e5d4ab2","parentId":"0c4e7c4d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:12:44.352Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-04-03 16:12 GMT-3] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Research and validate, using local OpenClaw docs first, the best way to ensure fresh/clean agent activation per run in this environment, and how supervisor-style agents should be instructed to prefer CLI invocation over ACP/sessions_spawn when orchestrating worker agents. Focus on: (1) whether `openclaw agent --agent ...` reuses agent sessions by design, (2) whether there is any documented way to force a fresh session/clean context for CLI agent turns, (3) how to structure instructions so a supervisor reliably launches all intended workers instead of drifting into ACP or subset execution. Then provide concrete guidance for the current B2/S3 Perseus integration. Do not edit files."}],"timestamp":1775243564326}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5ead7d3","parentId":"1e5d4ab2","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:12:48.305Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a subagent task focused on researching best practices for agent activation, session management, and supervisor-style orchestration in OpenClaw. The requester (main agent) wants me to:\n\n1. Research how `openclaw agent --agent ...` works (reuse vs fresh sessions)\n2. Find ways to force fresh session/clean context\n3. Understand how to structure supervisor instructions for reliable worker launching\n4. Apply findings to B2/S3 Perseus integration\n5. Use local OpenClaw docs first\n\nI should start by reading local OpenClaw documentation, then check any public docs or GitHub if needed. I should NOT edit files.\n\nLet me approach this systematically:\n1. Check workspace for any existing OpenClaw docs\n2. Look for OpenClaw CLI documentation\n3. Check if there's anything in node_modules about openclaw\n4. Look for any existing guidance on agent orchestration\n5. Apply to the Perseus integration context\n\nLet me start by exploring what's available.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"I'll research this systematically using local OpenClaw docs first, then synthesize guidance for the Perseus integration."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01TocBSpRzGUNGrmDZJFgDdY","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find \"~/.openclaw\" -name \"*.md\" -type f | grep -i \"agent\\|session\\|cli\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":332,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":14971,"totalTokens":15313,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0016600000000000002,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.01871375,"total":0.020383750000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775243564345,"responseId":"msg_01TVXYvJ1KsP6xRFSZsvgeYw"}}
